title: South Korea 5 Year Note Yield
description: South Korea 5 Year Bond Yield was 3.88 percent on Friday November 11, according to over-the-counter interbank yield quotes for this government bond maturity. Historically, the South Korea 5 Year Note Yield reached an all time high of 6.21 in July of 2008. This page includes a chart with historical data for South Korea 5Y.
